properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 4 at 7:50PM EST until January 5 at 10:00PM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
seas 7 to 9 feet nearshore, and up to 12 feet in the Gulf Stream.

* WHERE...Flagler Beach to Volusia-Brevard County Line 20-60 nm,
Volusia-Brevard County Line to Jupiter Inlet out to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 10 AM EST Sunday. For the
Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM to 10 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST SUNDAY... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 10 PM EST SUNDAY
